    <div class= "container">
      <div class="row-fluid">
        <div class= "span4">
           
        </div>
        <div class= "span3">
        </div>
        <div class= "span5 text-center", id= "right">
          
          <h4>Developing websites and apps as you read this.</h4>
          
          <%= link_to "Peruse my work", "#work", id: "site", class: "btn btn-large" %>
        </div>
      </div>
        <div class= "row-fluid", id= "about">
          <div class= "span4">
            <h1 id= "head">About me</h1>
          </div>

          <div class= "span8">
            <p>Four years in France was a rather long sabbatical that allowed me to find a passion for web development and also gave me the time to learn how to do it. I started out on a professional course learning Java but I soon moved onto teaching myself Ruby on Rails and I've never looked back. I enjoy creating web applications from a vague initial idea all the way to production. I get excited by both the creative nature of front end development and the problem solving nature of the back end. </br>When I'm not programming I'll be involved in sports (watching or playing), or books (writing or reading), with any other time spent in a bar of some description. </p>
          </div>
</div>
        
          <div class= "span12 text-center", id= "site">
            <h1 id="work">My sites</h1>
          </div>

          <div class= "row-fluid", id="breaks">
          <div class= "span6 text-center">
            <h5>This is a Peterborough utd fan site. It allows users to sign up to use the forum. Feel free to subscibe and discuss the Posh!</h5>
          </div>
          <div class= "span6">
            <div class= "text-center"><%= link_to image_tag("posh.png", alt: "Posh Website", id: "posh"), "http://theposh.herokuapp.com" %>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class= "row-fluid", id="breaks">
          <div class= "span6 text-center">
            <h5>This is a site I made in France. It's a weightlifting app that allows users to track their workouts and progress. I find it very helpful for use with the gym. You can also view the progress of other users and speak to them on the forum. There are also workout regimes that you can follow. The site is in French, be warned.</h5>
          </div>

          <div class= "span6">
            <div class= "text-center"><%= link_to image_tag("musc.png", alt: "Musculation Website", id: "musc"), "http://musculationprogramme.com" %>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class= "row-fluid", id="breaks">
          <div class= "span6 text-center">
            <h5>This is a site for a holiday log cabin. It is a simple site with information about how to book. It also comes with a map and an image slide show.</h5>
          </div>

          <div class= "span6">
            
            <div class= "text-center"><%= link_to image_tag("log.png", alt: "Log Cabin Website", id: "log"), "http://stamfordcabin.herokuapp.com" %>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

          

        
    </div>

